#technical stack

- Next.js (Node.js) for the backend (serverless functions)
- React with HTML/JS for the frontend (using client components and hooks)
- Firestore for database storage (no JSON file storage)
- Environment-specific configurations (using process.env and local storage)
- External API integration (GROQ API for chat completions)
- TypeScript for type safety and clarity
- React libraries for notifications (react-toastify) and Markdown rendering (ReactMarkdown)